g.text: After you’ve chosen a clinic, the preliminary process starts. Here you’ll need to run a series of tests.These may include but are not limited to a semen as-sessment and an ovarian assessment. If you’ve taken the tests elsewhere before choosing your clinic they should be dated within one year. Some-times, your clinic will insist on administering a new test. Whatever the case, the results of the tests will deter-mine the best treatment options.

After results are available, you’ll have your first consultation appointment. Your personal medical history and the results are examined. At this point, it’s your doctor’s job to give you the best recommendation based on your unique situation.
